The paper deals with computational geometry and the computation of zone and double zone diagrams, which are implicit geometric objects. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves iterative methods and algorithms for computing Voronoi diagrams, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses topological properties of Voronoi cells, which falls under the sub-category of geometric reasoning (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves the computation of geometric objects in a general setting, which could be considered as a system (cs.SY).
